son.param_description:
User Levels, different interception strategies can be configured for users of different levels. Possible values include:
0: Lowest level users, typically such as newly registered, completely inactive, or users with a level of 0;
1: Lower level users, typically such as low active or low-level users;
2: Mid-level users, typically such as users with certain activity or medium-level users;
3: Higher level users, typically such as highly active or high-level users;
4: Highest level users, typically such as paying users, VIP users, etc.

When riskLevel is PASS, return normal;
In other cases, display in the format: "First Level Label: Second Level Label: Third Level Label" in Chinese names.
This is only for human reference to understand the reasons for risk, and the program should not rely on the value of this parameter for logical processing.

